[normal] Research in Italy has found that a village where half the businesses are emloyee owned has a 
[normal]healthier community compared to a nearby village with no employee ownership. This encompassed more equality, larger social networks, children stayed at school longer, higher turnout at elections, less conspicuous consumption, more disposable income and les
[normal]s stress-related illnesses 
[normal](Erdall, David, 2011: 241)
